cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CY 

The paper deals with error-correcting codes and their applications in cryptography, which are topics covered in the sub-categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between locality and information rate, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of hash functions and expander graphs in the constructions suggests a connection to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
